Now for the second condition, we need to show that `(f - p).score L ≤ f.score L`. The score of a factorization is the sum of the logarithms of its prime factors (with multiplicity) up to L. When we remove `p`, we remove `log p` from the score:

```tactics
  · -- Show that (f - p).score L ≤ f.score L
    simp [Factorization.score]
