After simplification, we need to show that `∑ x ∈ (f - p).a, if x ≤ L then Real.log x else 0 ≤ ∑ x ∈ f.a, if x ≤ L then Real.log x else 0`. This is true because removing terms can only decrease or keep the same the sum:

